obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (49525)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49525&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Medical`
  line `Commission Act, 2019.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 2nd September, 2019---Sections 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 11, 16, 17, 18, 19, 56 and 57, vide notification No. S.O. 3162(E), dated 2nd`
  line `September, 2019, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `25th September, 2020--all the remaining provisions, vide notification No. S.O. 3262(E), dated 24th September, 2020, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3, Sub-section(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (49526)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49526&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) “Autonomous Board” means any of the Autonomous Boards constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(b) “Chairperson” means the Chairperson of the National Medical Commission appointed under`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) “Commission” means the National Medical Commission constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) “Council” means the Medical Advisory Council constituted under section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) “Ethics and Medical Registration Board” means the Board constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) “health University” means a University specialised in affiliating institutions engaged in`
  line `teaching medicine, medical and health sciences and includes a medical University and University of`
  line `health sciences;`
  line
  line `(g) “licence” means a licence to practice medicine granted under sub-section (1) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(h) “Medical Assessment and Rating Board” means the Board constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(i) “medical institution” means any institution within or outside India which grants degrees,`
  line `diplomas or licences in medicine and include affiliated colleges and deemed to be Universities;`
  line
  line `(j) “medicine” means modern scientific medicine in all its branches and includes surgery and`
  line `obstetrics, but does not include veterinary medicine and surgery;`
  line
  line `(k) “Member” means a Member of the Commission appointed under section 5 and includes the`
  line `Chairperson thereof;`
  line
  line `(l) “National Board of Examination” means the body registered as such under the Societies`
  line `Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) which grants broad-speciality and super-speciality qualifications`
  line `referred to in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(m) “National Register” means a National Medical Register maintained by the Ethics and Medical`
  line `Registration Board under section 31;`
  line
  line `(n) “notification” means notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression “notify”`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(o) “Post-Graduate Medical Education Board” means the Board constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(p) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(q) “President” means the President of an Autonomous Board appointed under section 18;`
  line
  line `(r) “recognised medical qualification” means a medical qualification recognised under section 35`
  line `or section 36 or section 37 or section 40, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(s) “regulations” means the regulations made by the Commission under this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) “Schedule” means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(u) “State Medical Council” means a medical council constituted under any law for the time`
  line `being in force in any State or Union territory for regulating the practice and registration of`
  line `practitioners of medicine in that State or Union territory;`
  line
  line `(v) “State Register” means a register maintained under any law for the time being in force in any`
  line `State or Union territory for registration of practitioners of medicine;`
  line
  line `(w) “Under-Graduate Medical Education Board” means the Board constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(x) “University” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (f) of section 2 of the`
  line `University Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956) and includes a health University.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (49527)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of National Medical Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49527&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute a`
  line `Commission, to be known as the National Medical Commission, to exercise the powers conferred upon,`
  line `and to perform the functions assigned to it, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property, both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Commission shall be at New Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (49528)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49528&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall consist of the following persons to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) ten ex officio Members; and`
  line
  line `(c) twenty-two part-time Members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall be a medical professional of outstanding ability, proven administrative`
  line `capacity and integrity, possessing a postgraduate degree in any discipline of medical sciences from any`
  line `University and having experience of not less than twenty years in the field of medical sciences, out of`
  line `which at least ten years shall be as a leader in the area of medical education.`
  line
  line `(3) The following persons shall be the ex officio Members of the Commission, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the President of the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the President of the Post-Graduate Medical Education Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the President of the Medical Assessment and Rating Board;`
  line
  line `(d) the President of the Ethics and Medical Registration Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the Director General of Health Services, Directorate General of Health Services, New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(f) the Director General, Indian Council of Medical Research;`
  line
  line `(g) a Director of any of the All India Institutes of Medical Sciences, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) two persons from amongst the Directors of Postgraduate Institute of Medical Education and`
  line `Research, Chandigarh; Jawaharlal Institute of Postgraduate Medical Education and Research,`
  line `Puducherry; Tata Memorial Hospital, Mumbai; North Eastern Indira Gandhi Regional Institute of`
  line `Health and Medical Sciences, Shillong; and All India Institute of Hygiene and Public Health,`
  line `Kolkata; to be nominated by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(i) one person to represent the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with Health and`
  line `Family Welfare, not below the rank of Additional Secretary to the Government of India, to be`
  line `nominated by that Ministry.`
  line
  line `(4) The following persons shall be appointed as part-time Members of the Commission, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) three Members to be appointed from amongst persons of ability, integrity and standing, who`
  line `have special knowledge and professional experience in such areas including management, law,`
  line `medical ethics, health research, consumer or patient rights advocacy, science and technology and`
  line economics;
  line
  line `(b) ten Members to be appointed on rotational basis from amongst the nominees of the States and`
  line `Union territories, under clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (2) of section 11, in the Medical Advisory`
  line `Council for a term of two years in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) nine members to be appointed from amongst the nominees of the States and Union territories,`
  line `under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 11, in the Medical Advisory Council for a term of two`
  line `years in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section and section 17, the term leader means the Head`
  line `of a Department or the Head of an organisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (49529)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Search Committee for appointment of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49529&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall appoint the Chairperson, part-time Members referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 4 and the Secretary referred to in section 8 on the recommendation of a Search Committee`
  line `consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Cabinet Secretary----Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) three experts, possessing outstanding qualifications and experience of not less than twentyfive years in the field of medical education, public health education and health research, to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government----Members;`
  line
  line `(c) one expert, from amongst the part-time Members referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 4, to be nominated by the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed----`
  line Member;
  line
  line `(d) one person, possessing outstanding qualifications and experience of not less than twenty-five`
  line `years in the field of management or law or economics or science and technology, to be nominated by`
  line `the Central Government—Member; and`
  line
  line `(e) the Secretary to the Government of India in charge of the Ministry of Health and Family`
  line `Welfare, to be the Convenor—Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, within one month from the date of occurrence of any vacancy,`
  line `including by reason of death, resignation or removal of the Chairperson or a Member, or within three`
  line `months before the end of tenure of the Chairperson or Member, make a reference to the Search`
  line `Committee for filling up of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The Search Committee shall recommend a panel of at least three names for every vacancy referred`
  line `to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The Search Committee shall, before recommending any person for appointment as the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member of the Commission, satisfy itself that such person does not have any financial`
  line `or other interest which is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as such Chairperson or Member.`
  line
  line `(5) No appointment of the Chairperson or Member shall be invalid merely by reason of any vacancy`
  line `or absence of a Member in the Search Committee.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) to (5), the Search Committee may regulate its own`
  line procedure.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (49530)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49530&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson`
  line `and the part-time Members, other than the part-time Members appointed under clauses (b) and (c) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4, shall hold office for a term not exceeding four years and shall not be eligible`
  line `for any extension or re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall cease to hold office after attaining the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio Member shall continue as long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is such Member.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a Member, other than an ex officio Member, is absent from three consecutive ordinary`
  line `meetings of the Commission and the cause of such absence is not attributable to any valid reason in the`
  line `opinion of the Commission, such Member shall be deemed to have vacated the seat.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Member, other than an ex officio Member, shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson or a Member may,--`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving in writing to the Central Government a notice of not less than`
  line `three months; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 7:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person may be relieved from duties earlier than three months or be allowed to`
  line `continue beyond three months until a successor is appointed, if the Central Government so decides.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairperson and every member of the Commission shall make declaration of his assets and`
  line `his liabilities at the time of entering upon his office and at the time of demitting his office and also declare`
  line `his professional and commercial engagement or involvement in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, and such declaration shall be published on the website of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson or a Member, ceasing to hold office as such, shall not accept, for a period of two`
  line `years from the date of demitting such office, any employment, in any capacity, including as a consultant`
  line `or an expert, in any private medical institution, whose matter has been dealt with by such Chairperson or`
  line `Member, directly or indirectly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein shall be construed as preventing such person from accepting an`
  line `employment in a body or institution, including medical institution, controlled or maintained by the`
  line `Central Government or a State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing herein shall prevent the Central Government from permitting the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member to accept any employment in any capacity, including as a consultant or expert`
  line `in any private medical institution whose matter has been dealt with by such Chairperson or Member.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (49531)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Removal of Chairperson and Member of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49531&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `order, remove from office the Chairperson or any other Member, who--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a Member; or`
  line
  line `(f) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) No Member shall be removed under clauses (e) and (f) of sub-section (1) unless he has been given`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (49532)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appointment of Secretary, experts, professionals, officers and other employees of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49532&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Secretariat for the Commission to be headed by a Secretary, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government in accordance with the provisions of section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) The Secretary of the Commission shall be a person of proven administrative capacity and`
  line `integrity, possessing such qualifications and experience as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary shall be appointed by the Central Government for a term of four years and shall not`
  line `be eligible for any extension or re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Secretary shall discharge such functions of the Commission as are assigned to him by the`
  line `Commission and as may be specified by regulations made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission may, for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act, appoint such`
  line `officers and other employees, as it considers necessary, against the posts created by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Secretary, officers and other employees of the Commission shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Commission may engage, in accordance with the procedure specified by regulations, such`
  line `number of experts and professionals of integrity and outstanding ability, who have special knowledge of,`
  line `and experience in such fields, including medical education, public health, management, health economics,`
  line `quality assurance, patient advocacy, health research, science and technology, administration, finance,`
  line `accounts and law, as it deems necessary, to assist the Commission in the discharge of its functions under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (49533)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Meetings, etc., of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49533&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet at least once every quarter at`
  line `such time and place as may be appointed by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall preside at the meeting of the Commission, and if, for any reason, the`
  line `Chairperson is unable to attend a meeting of the Commission, any other Member, being the President of`
  line `an Autonomous Board, nominated by the Chairperson, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the procedure to be followed at the meetings of the Commission is otherwise provided by`
  line `regulations, one-half of the total number of Members of the Commission including the Chairperson shall`
  line `constitute the quorum and all the acts of the Commission shall be decided by a majority of the members,`
  line `present and voting and in the event of equality of votes, the Chairperson, or in his absence, the President`
  line `of the Autonomous Board nominated under sub-section (2), shall have the casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) The general superintendence, direction and control of the administration of the Commission shall`
  line `vest in the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(5) No act done by the Commission shall be questioned on the ground of the existence of a vacancy`
  line `in, or a defect in the constitution of, the Commission.`
  line
  line `(6) A person who is aggrieved by any decision of the Commission except the decision rendered under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 30 may prefer an appeal to the Central Government against such decision within`
  line `thirty days of the communication of such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (49534)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers and functions of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49534&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall perform the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) lay down policies for maintaining a high quality and high standards in medical education and`
  line `make necessary regulations in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) lay down policies for regulating medical institutions, medical researches and medical`
  line `professionals and make necessary regulations in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) assess the requirements in healthcare, including human resources for health and healthcare`
  line `infrastructure and develop a road map for meeting such requirements;`
  line
  line `(d) promote, co-ordinate and frame guidelines and lay down policies by making necessary`
  line `regulations for the proper functioning of the Commission, the Autonomous Boards and the State`
  line `Medical Councils;`
  line
  line `(e) ensure co-ordination among the Autonomous Boards;`
  line
  line `(f) take such measures, as may be necessary, to ensure compliance by the State Medical Councils`
  line `of the guidelines framed and regulations made under this Act for their effective functioning under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(g) exercise appellate jurisdiction with respect to the decisions of the Autonomous Boards;`
  line
  line `(h) lay down policies and codes to ensure observance of professional ethics in medical profession`
  line `and to promote ethical conduct during the provision of care by medical practitioners;`
  line
  line `(i) frame guidelines for determination of fees and all other charges in respect of fifty per cent. of`
  line `seats in private medical institutions and deemed to be universities which are governed under the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the signature of the`
  line Secretary.
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may delegate such of its powers of administrative and financial matters, as it`
  line `deems fit, to the Secretary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission may constitute sub-committees and delegate such of its powers to such`
  line `sub-committees as may be necessary to enable them to accomplish specific tasks.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (49535)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Constitution and composition of Medical Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49535&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall constitute an advisory body to be known as the Medical Advisory Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall consist of a Chairperson and the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson of the Commission shall be the ex officio Chairperson of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) every member of the Commission shall be the ex officio members of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) one member to represent each State, who is the Vice-Chancellor of a health University in that`
  line `State, to be nominated by that State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) one member to represent each Union territory, who is the Vice-Chancellor of a health`
  line `University in that Union territory, to be nominated by the Ministry of Home Affairs in the`
  line `Government of India;`
  line
  line `(e) one member to represent each State and each Union territory from amongst elected members`
  line `of the State Medical Council, to be nominated by that State Medical Council;`
  line
  line `(f) the Chairman, University Grants Commission;`
  line
  line `(g) the Director, National Assessment and Accreditation Council;`
  line
  line `(h) four members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst persons holding the`
  line `post of Director in the Indian Institutes of Technology, Indian Institutes of Management and the`
  line `Indian Institute of Science:`
  line
  line `Provided that if there is no health University in any State or Union territory, the Vice-Chancellor`
  line `of a University within that State or Union territory having the largest number of medical colleges`
  line `affiliated to it shall be nominated by the State Government or by the Ministry of Home Affairs in the`
  line `Government of India:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if there is no University in any Union territory, the Ministry of Home`
  line `Affairs shall nominate a member who possesses such medical qualification and experience as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (49536)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of Medical Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49536&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall be the primary platform`
  line `through which the States and Union territories may put forth their views and concerns before the`
  line `Commission and help in shaping the overall agenda, policy and action relating to medical education and`
  line training.
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall advise the Commission on measures to determine and maintain, and to`
  line `co-ordinate maintenance of, the minimum standards in all matters relating to medical education, training`
  line `and research.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall advise the Commission on measures to enhance equitable access to medical`
  line education.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (49537)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Meetings of Medical Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49537&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall meet at least twice a year at`
  line `such time and place as may be decided by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall preside at the meeting of the Council and if for any reason the Chairperson`
  line `is unable to attend a meeting of the Council, such other member as nominated by the Chairperson shall`
  line `preside over the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the procedure is otherwise provided by regulations, fifty per cent. of the members of the`
  line `Council including the Chairperson shall form the quorum and all acts of the Council shall be decided by a`
  line `majority of the members present and voting.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (49538)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `National Eligibilitycum-Entrance Test.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49538&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a uniform National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test for admission to the undergraduate and postgraduate super-speciality medical education in`
  line `all medical institutions which are governed by the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the uniform National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test for admission to the undergraduate`
  line `medical education shall also be applicable to all medical institutions governed under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall conduct the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test in English and in such`
  line `other languages, through such designated authority and in such manner, as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall specify by regulations the manner of conducting common counselling by`
  line `the designated authority for admission to undergraduate and postgraduate super-speciality seats in all the`
  line `medical institutions which are governed by the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the designated authority of the Central Government shall conduct the common`
  line `counselling for all India seats and the designated authority of the State Government shall conduct the`
  line `common counselling for the seats at the State level.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (49539)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `National Exit Test.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49539&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) A common final year undergraduate medical examination, to be known`
  line `as the National Exit Test shall be held for granting licence to practice medicine as medical practitioners`
  line `and for enrolment in the State Register or the National Register, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall conduct the National Exit Test through such designated authority and in`
  line `such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Exit Test shall become operational on such date, within three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, as may be appointed by the Central Government, by notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person with a foreign medical qualification shall have to qualify National Exit Test for the`
  line `purpose of obtaining licence to practice medicine as medical practitioner and for enrolment in the State`
  line `Register or the National Register, as the case may be, in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Exit Test shall be the basis for admission to the postgraduate broad-speciality`
  line `medical education in medical institutions which are governed under the provisions of this Act or under`
  line `any other law for the time being in force and shall be done in such manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall specify by regulations the manner of conducting common counselling by`
  line `the designated authority for admission to the postgraduate broad-speciality seats in the medical`
  line `institutions referred to in sub-section (5):`
  line
  line `Provided that the designated authority of the Central Government shall conduct the common`
  line `counselling for All India seats and the designated authority of the State Government shall conduct the`
  line `common counselling for the seats at the State level.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (49540)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Constitution of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49540&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `constitute the following Autonomous Boards, under the overall supervision of the Commission, to`
  line `perform the functions assigned to such Boards under this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the Post-Graduate Medical Education Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the Medical Assessment and Rating Board; and`
  line
  line `(d) the Ethics and Medical Registration Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Board referred to in sub-section (1) shall be an autonomous body which shall carry out its`
  line `functions under this Act subject to the regulations made by the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (49541)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Composition of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49541&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Autonomous Board shall consist of a President`
  line `and two whole-time Members and two part-time Members.`
  line
  line `(2) The President of each Autonomous Board, three Members (including one part-time Member) of`
  line `the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board and the Post-Graduate Medical Education Board, and two`
  line `Members (including one part-time Member) each of the Medical Assessment and Rating Board and the`
  line `Ethics and Medical Registration Board shall be persons of outstanding ability, proven administrative capacity and integrity, possessing a postgraduate degree in any discipline of medical sciences from any`
  line `University and having experience of not less than fifteen years in such field, out of which at least seven`
  line `years shall be as a leader in the area of medical education, public health, community medicine or health`
  line research.
  line
  line `(3) The third Member of the Medical Assessment and Rating Board shall be a person of outstanding`
  line `ability and integrity, possessing a postgraduate degree in any of the disciplines of management, quality`
  line `assurance, law or science and technology from any University, having not less than fifteen years’`
  line `experience in such field, out of which at least seven years shall be as a leader.`
  line
  line `(4) The third Member of the Ethics and Medical Registration Board shall be a person of outstanding`
  line `ability who has demonstrated public record of work on medical ethics or a person of outstanding ability`
  line `possessing a postgraduate degree in any of the disciplines of quality assurance, public health, law or`
  line `patient advocacy from any University and having not less than fifteen years’ experience in such field, out`
  line `of which at least seven years shall be as a leader.`
  line
  line `(5) The fourth Member of each Autonomous Boards, being a part-time Member, shall be chosen from`
  line `amongst the elected Members of the State Medical Council in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (49542)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Search Committee for appointment of President and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49542&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `shall appoint the President and Members of the Autonomous Boards, except Members referred to in`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 17, on the recommendations made by the Search Committee constituted under`
  line `section 5 in accordance with the procedure specified in that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (49543)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of President and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49543&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President and`
  line `Members (other than part-time Members) of each Autonomous Board shall hold the office for a term not`
  line `exceeding four years and shall not be eligible for any extension or re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that part-time Members of each Autonomous Board shall hold the office for a term of two`
  line `years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a Member shall cease to hold office after attaining the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of the President`
  line `and Members (other than part-time Members) of an Autonomous Board shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that part-time Members of each Autonomous Board shall be entitled for such allowances as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (3), (5), (6), (7) and (8) of section 6 relating to other terms and`
  line `conditions of service of, and section 7 relating to removal from the office of, the Chairperson and`
  line `Members of the Commission shall also be applicable to the President and Members of the Autonomous`
  line Boards.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (49544)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Advisory committees of experts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes .
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49544&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Autonomous Board, except the Ethics and Medical`
  line `Registration Board, shall be assisted by such advisory committees of experts as may be constituted by the`
  line `Commission for the efficient discharge of the functions of such Boards under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ethics and Medical Registration Board shall be assisted by such ethics committees of experts`
  line `as may be constituted by the Commission for the efficient discharge of the functions of that Board under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (49545)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Staff of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49545&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The experts, professionals, officers and other employees`
  line `appointed under section 8 shall be made available to the Autonomous Boards in such number, and in such`
  line `manner, as may be specified by regulations by the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (49546)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Meetings, etc., of Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49546&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Autonomous Board shall meet at least once`
  line `a month at such time and place as it may appoint.`
  line
  line `(2) All decisions of the Autonomous Boards shall be made by majority of votes of the President and`
  line Members.
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provision of section 28, a person who is aggrieved by any decision of an`
  line `Autonomous Board may prefer an appeal to the Commission against such decision within sixty days of`
  line `the communication of such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (49547)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Powers of Autonomous Boards and delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49547&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of each`
  line `Autonomous Board shall have such administrative and financial powers as may be delegated to it by the`
  line `Commission to enable such Board to function efficiently.`
  line
  line `(2) The President of an Autonomous Board may further delegate any of his powers to a Member or an`
  line `officer of that Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (49548)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers and functions of UnderGraduate Medical Education Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49548&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The UnderGraduate Medical Education Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) determine standards of medical education at undergraduate level and oversee all aspects`
  line `relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) develop competency based dynamic curriculum at undergraduate level in accordance with the`
  line `regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) develop competency based dynamic curriculum for addressing the needs of primary health`
  line `services, community medicine and family medicine to ensure healthcare in such areas, in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of the regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) frame guidelines for setting up of medical institutions for imparting undergraduate courses,`
  line `having regard to the needs of the country and the global norms, in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `the regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) determine the minimum requirements and standards for conducting courses and examinations`
  line `for undergraduates in medical institutions, having regard to the needs of creativity at local levels,`
  line `including designing of some courses by individual institutions, in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `the regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) determine standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education in medical`
  line `institutions providing undergraduate medical education in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) facilitate development and training of faculty members teaching undergraduate courses;`
  line
  line `(h) facilitate research and the international student and faculty exchange programmes relating to`
  line `undergraduate medical education;`
  line
  line `(i) specify norms for compulsory annual disclosures, electronically or otherwise, by medical`
  line `institutions, in respect of their functions that has a bearing on the interest of all stakeholders including`
  line `students, faculty, the Commission and the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(j) grant recognition to a medical qualification at the undergraduate level.`
  line
  line `(2) The Under-Graduate Medical Education Board may, in the discharge of its duties, make such`
  line `recommendations to, and seek such directions from, the Commission, as it deems necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (49549)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Powers and functions of Post-Graduate Medical Education Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49549&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Post-Graduate`
  line `Medical Education Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) determine the standards of medical education at the postgraduate level and super-speciality`
  line `level in accordance with the regulations made under this Act and oversee all aspects relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) develop competency based dynamic curriculum at postgraduate level and super-speciality`
  line `level in accordance with the regulations made under this Act, with a view to develop appropriate skill,`
  line `knowledge, attitude, values and ethics among postgraduates and super-specialists to provide`
  line `healthcare, impart medical education and conduct medical research;`
  line
  line `(c) frame guidelines for setting up of medical institutions for imparting postgraduate and`
  line `super-speciality courses, having regard to the needs of the country and global norms, in accordance`
  line `with the regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) determine the minimum requirements and standards for conducting postgraduate and`
  line `super-speciality courses and examinations in medical institution, in accordance with the regulations`
  line `made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) determine standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education in medical`
  line `institutions conducting postgraduate and super-speciality medical education, in accordance with the`
  line `regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) facilitate development and training of the faculty members teaching postgraduate and superspeciality courses;`
  line
  line `(g) facilitate research and the international student and faculty exchange programmes relating to`
  line `postgraduate and super-speciality medical education;`
  line
  line `(h) specify norms for compulsory annual disclosure, electronically or otherwise, by medical`
  line `institutions in respect of their functions that has a bearing on the interest of all stakeholders including`
  line `students, faculty, the Commission and the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) grant recognition to the medical qualifications at the postgraduate level and super-speciality`
  line level;
  line
  line `(j) promote and facilitate postgraduate courses in family medicine.`
  line
  line `(2) The Post-Graduate Medical Education Board may, in the discharge of its functions, make such`
  line `recommendations to, and seek such directions from, the Commission, as it deems necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (49550)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Powers and functions of Medical Assessment and Rating Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49550&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Medical`
  line `Assessment and Rating Board shall perform the following functions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) determine the procedure for assessing and rating the medical institutions for their compliance`
  line `with the standards laid down by the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate`
  line `Medical Education Board, as the case may be, in accordance with the regulations made under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(b) grant permission for establishment of a new medical institution, or to start any postgraduate`
  line `course or to increase number of seats, in accordance with the provisions of section 28;`
  line
  line `(c) carry out inspections of medical institutions for assessing and rating such institutions in`
  line `accordance with the regulations made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Medical Assessment and Rating Board may, if it deems necessary, hire and`
  line `authorise any other third party agency or persons for carrying out inspections of medical institutions`
  line `for assessing and rating such institutions:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where inspection of medical institutions is carried out by such third party`
  line `agency or persons authorised by the Medical Assessment and Rating Board, it shall be obligatory on`
  line `such institutions to provide access to such agency or person;`
  line
  line `(d) conduct, or where it deems necessary, empanel independent rating agencies to conduct, assess`
  line `and rate all medical institutions, within such period of their opening, and every year thereafter, at such`
  line `time, and in such manner, as may be specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(e) make available on its website or in public domain the assessment and ratings of medical`
  line `institutions at regular intervals in accordance with the regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) take such measures, including issuing warning, imposition of monetary penalty, reducing`
  line `intake or stoppage of admissions and recommending to the Commission for withdrawal of`
  line `recognition, against a medical institution for failure to maintain the minimum essential standards`
  line `specified by the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical Education`
  line `Board, as the case may be, in accordance with the regulations made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Medical Assessment and Rating Board may, in the discharge of its functions, make such`
  line `recommendations to, and seek such directions from, the Commission, as it deems necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (49551)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Powers and functions of Ethics and Medical Registration Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49551&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ethics and Medical`
  line `Registration Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) maintain National Registers of all licensed medical practitioners in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 31;`
  line
  line `(b) regulate professional conduct and promote medical ethics in accordance with the regulations`
  line `made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Ethics and Medical Registration Board shall ensure compliance of the code of`
  line `professional and ethical conduct through the State Medical Council in a case where such State`
  line `Medical Council has been conferred power to take disciplinary actions in respect of professional or`
  line `ethical misconduct by medical practitioners under respective State Acts;`
  line
  line `(c) develop mechanisms to have continuous interaction with State Medical Councils to effectively`
  line `promote and regulate the conduct of medical practitioners and professionals;`
  line
  line `(d) exercise appellate jurisdiction with respect to the actions taken by a State Medical Council`
  line `under section 30.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ethics and Medical Registration Board may, in the discharge of its duties, make such`
  line `recommendations to, and seek such directions from, the Commission, as it deems necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (49552)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Permission for establishment of new medical college.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49552&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall establish a new`
  line `medical college or start any postgraduate course or increase number of seats without obtaining prior`
  line `permission of the Medical Assessment and Rating Board.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of obtaining permission under sub-section (1), a person may submit a scheme to`
  line `the Medical Assessment and Rating Board in such form, containing such particulars, accompanied by`
  line `such fee, and in such manner, as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Medical Assessment and Rating Board shall, having due regard to the criteria specified in`
  line `section 29, consider the scheme received under sub-section (2) and either approve or disapprove such`
  line `scheme within a period of six months from the date of such receipt:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disapproving such scheme, an opportunity to rectify the defects, if any, shall be`
  line `given to the person concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a scheme is approved under sub-section (3), such approval shall be the permission under`
  line `sub-section (1) to establish new medical college.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a scheme is disapproved under sub-section (3), or where no decision is taken within six`
  line `months of submitting a scheme under sub-section (1), the person concerned may prefer an appeal to the`
  line `Commission for approval of the scheme within fifteen days of such disapproval or, as the case may be,`
  line `lapse of six months, in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall decide the appeal received under sub-section (5) within a period of`
  line `forty-five days from the date of receipt of the appeal and in case the Commission approves the scheme,`
  line `such approval shall be the permission under sub-section (1) to establish a new medical college and in case`
  line `the Commission disapproves the scheme, or fails to give its decision within the specified period, the`
  line `person concerned may prefer a second appeal to the Central Government within thirty days of`
  line `communication of such disapproval or, as the case may be, lapse of specified period.`
  line
  line `(7) The Medical Assessment and Rating Board may conduct evaluation and assessment of any`
  line `medical institution at any time, either directly or through any other expert having integrity and experience`
  line `of medical profession and without any prior notice and assess and evaluate the performance, standards`
  line `and benchmarks of such medical institution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the term “person” includes a University, trust or any`
  line `other association of persons or body of individuals, but does not include the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (49553)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Criteria for approving or disapproving scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49553&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `While approving or disapproving a scheme`
  line `under section 28, the Medical Assessment and Rating Board, or the Commission, as the case may be,`
  line `shall take into consideration the following criteria, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) adequacy of financial resources;`
  line
  line `(b) whether adequate academic faculty and other necessary facilities have been provided to`
  line `ensure proper functioning of medical college or would be provided within the time-limit specified in`
  line `the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) whether adequate hospital facilities have been provided or would be provided within the`
  line `time-limit specified in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(d) such other factors as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that, subject to the previous approval of the Central Government, the criteria may be`
  line `relaxed for the medical colleges which are set up in such areas as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (49554)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `State Medical Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49554&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, within three years of the`
  line `commencement of this Act, take necessary steps to establish a State Medical Council if no such Council`
  line `exists in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a State Act confers power upon the State Medical Council to take disciplinary actions in`
  line `respect of any professional or ethical misconduct by a registered medical practitioner or professional, the`
  line `State Medical Council shall act in accordance with the regulations made, and the guidelines framed, under`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time as a State Medical Council is established in a State, the Ethics and`
  line `Medical Registration Board shall receive the complaints and grievances relating to any professional or`
  line `ethical misconduct against a registered medical practitioner or professional in that State in accordance`
  line `with such procedure as may be specified by the regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Ethics and Medical Registration Board or, as the case may be, the State`
  line `Medical Council shall give an opportunity of hearing to the medical practitioner or professional`
  line `concerned before taking any action, including imposition of any monetary penalty against such person.`
  line
  line `(3) A medical practitioner or professional who is aggrieved by any action taken by a State Medical`
  line `Council under sub-section (2) may prefer an appeal to the Ethics and Medical Registration Board against`
  line `such action, and the decision, if any, of the Ethics and Medical Registration Board thereupon shall be`
  line `binding on the State Medical Council, unless a second appeal is preferred under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(4) A medical practitioner or professional who is aggrieved by the decision of the Ethics and Medical`
  line `Registration Board may prefer an appeal to the Commission within sixty days of communication of such`
  line decision.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) “State” includes Union territory and the expressions “State Government” and “State Medical`
  line `Council”, in relation to a Union territory, shall respectively mean the “Central Government” and`
  line `“Union territory Medical Council”;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression “professional or ethical misconduct” includes any act of commission or`
  line `omission as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (49555)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `National Register and State Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49555&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ethics and Medical Registration Board shall`
  line `maintain a National Register containing the name, address, all recognised qualifications possessed by a`
  line `licensed medical practitioner and such other particulars as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Register shall be maintained in such form, including electronic form, in such`
  line `manner, as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The manner in which a name or qualification may be added to, or removed from, the National`
  line `Register and the grounds for removal thereof, shall be such as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) The National Register shall be a public document within the meaning of section 74 of the Indian`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line
  line `(5) The National Register shall be made available to the public by placing it on the website of the`
  line `Ethics and Medical Registration Board.`
  line
  line `(6) Every State Medical Council shall maintain and regularly update the State Register in the`
  line `specified electronic format and supply a physical copy of the same to the Ethics and Medical Registration`
  line `Board within three months of the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) The Ethics and Medical Registration Board shall ensure electronic synchronisation of the National`
  line `Register and the State Register in such a manner that any change in one register is automatically reflected`
  line `in the other register.`
  line
  line `(8) The Ethics and Medical Registration Board shall maintain a separate National Register in such`
  line `form, containing such particulars, including the name, address and all recognised qualifications possessed`
  line `by a Community Health Provider referred to in section 32 in such manner as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (49556)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Community Health Provider.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49556&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may grant limited licence to practice`
  line `medicine at mid-level as Community Health Provider to such person connected with modern scientific`
  line `medical profession who qualify such criteria as may be specified by the regulations:.`
  line
  line `Provided that the number of limited licence to be granted under this sub-section shall not exceed`
  line `one-third of the total number of licenced medical practitioners registered under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 31.
  line
  line `(2) The Community Health Provider who is granted limited licences under sub-section (1), may`
  line `practice medicine to such extent, in such circumstances and for such period, as may be specified by the`
  line regulations..
  line
  line `(3) The Community Health Provider may prescribe specified medicine independently, only in primary`
  line `and preventive healthcare, but in cases other than primary and preventive healthcare, he may prescribe`
  line `medicine only under the supervision of medical practitioners registered under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 32.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (49586)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Rights of persons to have licence to practice and to be enrolled in National Register or State Register and their obligations thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49586&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who qualifies the National Exit Test held under`
  line `section 15 shall be granted a licence to practice medicine and shall have his name and qualifications`
  line `enrolled in the National Register or a State Register, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who has been registered in the Indian Medical Register maintained under the`
  line `Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956) prior to the coming into force of this Act and before the`
  line `National Exit Test becomes operational under sub-section (3) of section 15, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `registered under this Act and be enrolled in the National Register maintained under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No person who has obtained medical qualification from a medical institution established in any`
  line `country outside India and is recognised as a medical practitioner in that country, shall, after the`
  line `commencement of this Act and the National Exit Test becomes operational under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 15, be enrolled in the National Register unless he qualifies the National Exit Test.`
  line
  line `(3) When a person whose name is entered in the State Register or the National Register, as the case`
  line `may be, obtains any title, diploma or other qualification for proficiency in sciences or public health or`
  line `medicine which is a recognised medical qualification under section 35 or section 36, as the case may be,`
  line `he shall be entitled to have such title, diploma or qualification entered against his name in the State`
  line `Register or the National Register, as the case may be, in such manner as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (49558)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Bar to practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49558&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than a person who is enrolled in the State Register or the`
  line `National Register, as the case may be, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be allowed to practice medicine as a qualified medical practitioner;`
  line
  line `(b) hold office as a physician or surgeon or any other office, by whatever name called, which is`
  line `meant to be held by a physician or surgeon;`
  line
  line `(c) be entitled to sign or authenticate a medical or fitness certificate or any other certificate`
  line `required by any law to be signed or authenticated by a duly qualified medical practitioner;`
  line
  line `(d) be entitled to give evidence at any inquest or in any court of law as an expert under section 45`
  line `of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) on any matter relating to medicine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission shall submit a list of such medical professionals to the Central`
  line `Government in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a foreign citizen who is enrolled in his country as a medical practitioner in`
  line `accordance with the law regulating the registration of medical practitioners in that country may be`
  line `permitted temporary registration in India for such period and in such manner as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes any of the provisions of this section shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (49559)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Recognition of medical qualifications granted by Universities or medical institutions in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49559&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The medical qualification granted by any University or medical institution in India shall be`
  line `listed and maintained by the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical`
  line `Education Board, as the case may be, in such manner as may be specified by the regulations and such`
  line `medical qualification shall be a recognised medical qualification for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any University or medical institution in India which grants an undergraduate or postgraduate or`
  line `super-speciality medical qualification not included in the list maintained by the Under-Graduate Medical`
  line `Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical Education Board, as the case may be, may apply to that`
  line `Board for granting recognition to such qualification.`
  line
  line `(3) The Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical Education Board, as`
  line `the case may be, shall examine the application for grant of recognition to a medical qualification within a`
  line `period of six months in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical Education`
  line `Board, as the case may be, decides to grant recognition to a medical qualification, it shall include such`
  line `medical qualification in the list maintained by it and also specify the date of effect of such recognition.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical Education`
  line `Board, as the case may be, decides not to grant recognition to a medical qualification, the University or`
  line `the medical institution concerned may prefer an appeal to the Commission for grant of recognition within`
  line `sixty days of the communication of such decision, in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall examine the appeal received under sub-section (5) within a period of two`
  line `months and if it decides that recognition may be granted to such medical qualification, it may direct the`
  line `Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical Education Board, as the case`
  line `may be, to include such medical qualification in the list maintained by that Board, in such manner as may`
  line `be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the Commission decides not to grant recognition to the medical qualification, or fails to`
  line `take a decision within the specified period, the University or the medical institution concerned may prefer`
  line `a second appeal to the Central Government within thirty days of the communication of such decision or`
  line `lapse of specified period, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(8) All medical qualifications which have been recognised before the date of commencement of this`
  line `Act and are included in the First Schedule and Part I of the Third Schedule to the Indian Medical Council`
  line `Act, 1956 (102 of 1956), shall also be recognised medical qualifications for the purposes of this Act, and`
  line `shall be listed and maintained by the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate`
  line `Medical Education Board, as the case may be, in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (49560)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Recognition of medical qualifications granted by medical institutions outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49560&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an authority in any country outside India, which by the law of that country is entrusted with the`
  line `recognition of medical qualifications in that country, makes an application to the Commission for`
  line `granting recognition to such medical qualification in India, the Commission may, subject to such`
  line `verification as it may deem necessary, either grant or refuse to grant recognition to that medical`
  line `qualification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission shall give a reasonable opportunity of being heard to such authority`
  line `before refusing to grant such recognition.`
  line
  line `(2) A medical qualification which is granted recognition by the Commission under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be a recognised medical qualification for the purposes of this Act, and such qualification shall be`
  line `listed and maintained by the Commission in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Commission refuses to grant recognition to the medical qualification under`
  line `sub-section (1), the authority concerned may prefer an appeal to the Central Government against such`
  line `decision within thirty days of communication thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) All medical qualifications which have been recognised before the date of commencement of this`
  line `Act and are included in the Second Schedule and Part II of the Third Schedule to the Indian Medical`
  line `Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956), shall also be recognised medical qualifications for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, and shall be listed and maintained by the Commission in such manner as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (49561)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Recognition of medical qualifications granted by statutory or other body in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49561&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `medical qualifications granted by any statutory or other body in India which are covered by the categories`
  line `listed in the Schedule shall be recognised medical qualifications for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Diplomate of National Board in broad-speciality qualifications and superspeciality`
  line `qualifications when granted in a medical institution with attached hospital or in a hospital with the`
  line `strength of five hundred or more beds, by the National Board of Examinations, shall be equivalent in all`
  line `respects to the corresponding postgraduate qualification and the super-speciality qualification granted`
  line `under this Act, but in all other cases, senior residency in a medical college for an additional period of one`
  line `year shall be required for such qualification to be equivalent for the purposes of teaching also.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Commission, and having regard to`
  line `the objects of this Act, by notification, add to, or, as the case may be, omit from, the Schedule any`
  line `categories of medical qualifications granted by a statutory or other body in India and on such addition, or`
  line `as the case may be, omission, the medical qualifications granted by such statutory or other body in India`
  line `shall be, or shall cease to be, recognised medical qualifications for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (49587)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Withdrawal of recognition granted to medical qualification granted by medical institutions in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49587&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, upon receiving a report from the Medical Assessment and Rating Board under`
  line `section 26, or otherwise, if the Commission is of the opinion that--`
  line
  line `(a) the courses of study and examination to be undergone in, or the proficiency required from`
  line `candidates at any examination held by, a University or medical institution do not conform to the`
  line `standards specified by the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical`
  line `Education Board, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) the standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education in medical`
  line `institution as determined by the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate`
  line `Medical Education Board, as the case may be, are not adhered to by any University or medical`
  line `institution, and such University or medical institution has failed to take necessary corrective action to maintain specified minimum standards, the Commission may initiate action in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission shall, before taking any action for suo motu withdrawal of recognition`
  line `granted to the medical qualification awarded by a University or medical institution, impose penalty in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 26.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, after making such further inquiry as it deems fit, and after holding`
  line `consultations with the concerned State Government and the authority of the concerned University or`
  line `medical institution, comes to the conclusion that the recognition granted to a medical qualification ought`
  line `to be withdrawn, it may, by order, withdraw recognition granted to such medical qualification and direct`
  line `the Under-Graduate Medical Education Board or the Post-Graduate Medical Education Board, as the case`
  line `may be, to amend the entries against the University or medical institution concerned in the list maintained`
  line `by that Board to the effect that the recognition granted to such medical qualification is withdrawn with`
  line `effect from the date specified in that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (49563)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Derecognition of medical qualifications granted by medical institutions outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49563&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Where, after verification with the authority in any country outside India, the Commission is of the opinion`
  line `that a recognised medical qualification which is included in the list maintained by it is to be derecognised,`
  line `it may, by order, derecognise such medical qualification and remove it from the list maintained by the`
  line `Commission with effect from the date of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (49564)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Special provision in certain cases for recognition of medical qualifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49564&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Where the`
  line `Commission deems it necessary, it may, by an order published in the Official Gazette, direct that any`
  line `medical qualification granted by a medical institution in a country outside India, after such date as may be`
  line `specified in that notification, shall be a recognised medical qualification for the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that medical practice by a person possessing such qualification shall be permitted only if`
  line `such person qualifies National Exit Test.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (49565)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49565&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Commission grants of such sums of money as the Central`
  line `Government may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (49566)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `National Medical Commission Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49566&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a fund to be called the`
  line `National Medical Commission Fund which shall form part of the public account of India and there shall`
  line `be credited thereto---`
  line
  line `(a) all Government grants, fees, penalties and charges received by the Commission and the`
  line `Autonomous Boards;`
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Commission from such other sources as may be decided by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for making payment towards---`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and Members of the Commission, the`
  line `Presidents and Members of the Autonomous Boards and the administrative expenses including the`
  line `salaries and allowances payable to the officers and other employees of the Commission and`
  line `Autonomous Boards;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses incurred in carrying out the provisions of this Act, including in connection with`
  line `the discharge of the functions of the Commission and the Autonomous Boards.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (49567)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Audit and accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49567&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed, in consultation`
  line `with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other persons appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Commission shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of, and complete access to, records, books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents`
  line `and papers and to inspect the office of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Commission as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be`
  line `forwarded annually by the Commission to the Central Government which shall cause the same to be laid,`
  line `as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (49568)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Furnishing of returns and reports to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49568&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall`
  line `furnish to the Central Government, at such time, in such form and in such manner, as may be prescribed`
  line `or as the Central Government may direct, such reports and statements, containing such particulars in`
  line `regard to any matter under the jurisdiction of the Commission, as the Central Government may, from time`
  line `to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall prepare, once every year, in such form and at such time as may be`
  line `prescribed, an annual report, giving a summary of its activities during the previous year and copies of the`
  line `report shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid by the Central Government, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (49569)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions to Commission and Autonomous Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49569&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the Commission and the Autonomous`
  line `Boards shall, in exercise of their powers and discharge of their functions under this Act, be bound by such`
  line `directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give in writing to them from time to`
  line `time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission and the Autonomous Boards shall, as far as practicable, be given an`
  line `opportunity to express their views before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (49570)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions to State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49570&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may give such directions, as it may deem necessary, to a State Government for carrying out`
  line `all or any of the provisions of this Act and the State Government shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (49571)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Information to be furnished by Commission and publication thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49571&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission`
  line `shall furnish such reports, copies of its minutes, abstracts of its accounts, and other information to the`
  line `Central Government as that Government may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may publish, in such manner as it may think fit, the reports, minutes,`
  line `abstracts of accounts and other information furnished to it under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (49572)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Obligation of universities and medical institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49572&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Every University and medical institution`
  line `governed under this Act shall maintain a website at all times and display on its website all such`
  line `information as may be required by the Commission or an Autonomous Board, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (49573)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Completion of courses of studies in medical institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49573&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, any student who was studying for a degree, diploma or certificate in any medical`
  line `institution immediately before the commencement of this Act shall continue to so study and complete his`
  line `course for such degree, diploma or certificate, and such institution shall continue to provide instructions`
  line `and examination for such student in accordance with the syllabus and studies as existed before such`
  line `commencement, and such student shall be deemed to have completed his course of study under this Act`
  line `and shall be awarded degree, diploma or certificate under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where recognition granted to a medical institution`
  line `has lapsed, whether by efflux of time or by its voluntary surrender or for any other reason whatsoever,`
  line `such medical institution shall continue to maintain and provide the minimum standards required to be`
  line `provided under this Act till such time as all candidates who are admitted in that medical institution`
  line `complete their study.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (49588)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Joint sittings of Commission, Central Councils of Homoeopathy and Indian medicine to enhance interface between their respective systems of medicine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49588&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a joint sitting of`
  line `the Commission, the Central Council of Homoeopathy and the Central Council of Indian Medicine at`
  line `least once a year, at such time and place as they mutually appoint, to enhance the interface between`
  line `Homoeopathy, Indian Systems of Medicine and modern systems of medicine.`
  line
  line `(2) The agenda for the joint sitting may be prepared with mutual agreement between the Chairpersons`
  line `of the Commission, the Central Council of Homoeopathy and the Central Council of Indian Medicine or`
  line `be prepared separately by each of them.`
  line
  line `(3) The joint sitting referred to in sub-section (1) may, by an affirmative vote of all members present`
  line `and voting, decide on approving specific educational modules or programmes that may be introduced in`
  line `the undergraduate course and the postgraduate course across medical systems and promote medical`
  line pluralism.
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (49575)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `State Government to promote primary healthcare in rural areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49575&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Every State Government`
  line `may, for the purposes of addressing or promoting primary healthcare in rural area, take necessary`
  line `measures to enhance the capacity of the healthcare professionals.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (49576)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Chairperson, Members, officers of Commission and of Autonomous Boards to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49576&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Members, officers and other employees of the Commission and the`
  line `President, Members and officers and other employees of the Autonomous Boards shall be deemed, when`
  line `acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within`
  line `the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code 1860 (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (49577)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49577&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government, the Commission or any Autonomous Board or a State Medical Council or any`
  line `Committee thereof, or any officer or other employee of the Government or of the Commission acting`
  line `under this Act for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules`
  line `or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (49578)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49578&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act`
  line `except upon a complaint in writing made in this behalf by an officer authorised by the Commission or the`
  line `Ethics and Medical Registration Board or a State Medical Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (49579)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49579&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `1) If, at any time, the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that---`
  line
  line `(a) the Commission is unable to discharge the functions and duties imposed on it by or under the`
  line `provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Commission has persistently made default in complying with any direction issued by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, supersede the Commission for such period, not exceeding`
  line `six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section, the Central Government shall give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the Commission to show cause as to why it should not be superseded and shall`
  line `consider the explanations and objections, if any, of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Commission,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the Members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Commission, shall, until the Commission is`
  line `re-constituted under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the`
  line `Central Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Commission shall, until the Commission is`
  line `re-constituted under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government may,---`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further term not exceeding six months, as it may`
  line `consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) re-constitute the Commission by fresh appointment and in such case the Members who`
  line `vacated their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed disqualified for`
  line `appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, whether as originally specified under sub-section (1) or as extended under this sub-section,`
  line `take action under clause (b) of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before both`
  line `Houses of Parliament at the earliest opportunity.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (49580)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49580&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointing six Members of the Commission on rotational basis from amongst`
  line `the nominees of the States and Union territories in the Medical Advisory Council under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of appointing five members of the Commission under clause (c) of sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of nominating one expert by the Central Government under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) the salary and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson and Members under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and the manner of making declaration under sub-section (6) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications and experience to be possessed by the Secretary of the Commission under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(g) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Secretary, officers and other employees of the Commission under sub-section (6) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(h) the other powers and functions of the Commission under clause (j) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `(i) the medical qualification and experience to be possessed by a member under the second`
  line `proviso to section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of choosing part-time Members under sub-section (5) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(k) the salary and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `President and Members of an Autonomous Board under sub-section (2), and the allowances payable`
  line `to part-time Members under the proviso thereunder, of section 19;`
  line
  line `(l) the other factors under clause (d) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of submitting a list of medical professionals under the second proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(n) the form for preparing annual statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(o) the time within which, and the form and the manner in which, the reports and statements shall`
  line `be furnished by the Commission and the particulars with regard to any matter as may be required by`
  line `the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(p) the form and the time for preparing annual report under sub-section (2) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(q) any other matter in respect of which provision is to be made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (49581)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49581&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may, after previous publication, by`
  line `notification, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the functions to be discharged by the Secretary of the Commission under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure in accordance with which experts and professionals may be engaged and the`
  line `number of such experts and professionals under sub-section (7) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed at the meetings of Commission, including the quorum at its`
  line `meetings under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the quality and standards to be maintained in medical education under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of regulating medical institutions, medical researches and medical professionals`
  line `under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of functioning of the Commission, the Autonomous Boards and the State Medical`
  line `Councils under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure to be followed at the meetings of the Medical Advisory Council, including the`
  line `quorum at its meetings under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(h) the other languages in which and the manner in which the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance`
  line `Test shall be conducted under sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of conducting common counselling by the designated authority for admission to`
  line `the undergraduate and postgraduate super-speciality medical education under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(j) the designated authority, and the manner for conducting the National Exit Test under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which a person with foreign medical qualification shall qualify National Exit`
  line `Test under sub-section (4) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner in which admission to the postgraduate broad-speciality medical education shall be`
  line `made on the basis of National Exit Test under sub-section (5) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of conducting common counselling by the designated authority for admission to`
  line `the postgraduate broad-speciality medical education under sub-section (6) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(n) the number of, and the manner in which, the experts, professionals, officers and other`
  line `employees shall be made available by the Commission to the Autonomous Boards under section 21;`
  line
  line `(o) the curriculum at undergraduate level under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(p) the curriculum for primary medicine, community medicine and family medicine under clause`
  line `(c) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner of imparting undergraduate courses by medical institutions under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(r) the minimum requirements and standards for conducting courses and examinations for`
  line `undergraduates in medical institutions under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(s) the standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education at undergraduate`
  line `level in medical institutions under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(t) the standards of medical education at the postgraduate level and superspeciality level under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(u) the curriculum at postgraduate level and super-speciality level under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of imparting postgraduate and super-speciality courses by medical institutions`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(w) the minimum requirements and standards for conducting postgraduate and super-speciality`
  line `courses and examinations in medical institutions under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(x) the standards and norms for infrastructure, faculty and quality of education in medical`
  line `institutions conducting postgraduate and super-speciality medical education under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(y) the procedure for assessing and rating the medical institutions under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(z) the manner of carrying out inspections of medical institutions for assessing and rating such`
  line `institutions under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(za) the manner of conducting, and the manner of empanelling independent rating agencies to`
  line `conduct, assessment and rating of medical institutions under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(zb) the manner of making available on website or in public domain the assessment and ratings of`
  line `medical institutions under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(zc) the measures to be taken against a medical institution for its failure to maintain the minimum`
  line `essential standards under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(zd) the manner of regulating professional conduct and promoting medical ethics under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(ze) the form of scheme, the particulars thereof, the fee to be accompanied and the manner of`
  line `submitting scheme for establishing a new medical college or for starting any postgraduate course or`
  line `for increasing number of seats under sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(zf) the manner of making an appeal to the Commission for approval of the scheme under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(zg) the areas in respect of which criteria may be relaxed under the proviso to section 29;`
  line
  line `(zh) the manner of taking disciplinary action by a State Medical Council for professional or`
  line `ethical misconduct of registered medical practitioner or professional and the procedure for receiving`
  line `complaints and grievances by Ethics and Medical Registration Board, under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(zi) the act of commission or omission which amounts to professional or ethical misconduct under`
  line `clause (b) of the Explanation to section 30;`
  line
  line `(zj) other particulars to be contained in a National Register under sub-section (1) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(zk) the form, including the electronic form and the manner of maintaining the National Register`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(zl) the manner in which any name or qualification may be added to, or removed from, the`
  line `National Register and the grounds for removal thereof, under sub-section (3) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(zm) the form and manner in which the National Register for registering Community Health`
  line `Provider is to be maintained under sub-section (8) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(zn) the criteria for granting limited licence to practice medicine under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 32;
  line
  line `(zo) the extent, the circumstances and the period under sub-section (2) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(zp) the manner of listing and maintaining medical qualifications granted by a University or`
  line `medical institution in India under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(zq) the manner of examining the application for grant of recognition under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 35;`
  line
  line `(zr) the manner of preferring an appeal to the Commission for grant of recognition under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(zs) the manner of including a medical qualification in the list maintained by the Board under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(zt) the manner of listing and maintaining medical qualifications which have been granted`
  line `recognition before the date of commencement of this Act under sub-section (8) of section 35.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (49582)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49582&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made,`
  line `and every notification issued, under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or regulation or notification; both Houses agree that the rule or regulation or notification`
  line `should not be made, the rule or regulation or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (49583)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49583&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary, for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (49584)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49584&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may appoint in`
  line `this behalf, the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956) shall stand repealed and the Medical`
  line `Council of India constituted under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the said Act shall stand dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Act referred to in sub-section (1), it shall not affect,--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of the Act so repealed or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or (b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the Act so`
  line `repealed; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty incurred in respect of any contravention under the Act so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(d) any proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege, obligation, liability, penalty`
  line `as aforesaid, and any such proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any`
  line `such penalty may be imposed as if that Act had not been repealed.`
  line
  line `(3) On the dissolution of the Medical Council of India, the person appointed as the Chairman of the`
  line `Medical Council of India and every other person appointed as the Member and any officer and other`
  line `employee of that Council and holding office as such immediately before such dissolution shall vacate`
  line `their respective offices and such Chairman and other Members shall be entitled to claim compensation not`
  line `exceeding three months' pay and allowances for the premature termination of term of their office or of`
  line `any contract of service:`
  line
  line `Provided that any officer or other employee who has been, immediately before the dissolution of the`
  line `Medical Council of India appointed on deputation basis to the Medical Council of India, shall, on such`
  line `dissolution, stand reverted to his parent cadre, Ministry or Department, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any officer or other employee who has been, immediately before the dissolution`
  line `of the Medical Council of India, employed on regular or contractual basis by the Medical Council of`
  line `India, shall, on and from such dissolution, cease to be the officer or employee of the Medical Council of`
  line `India and his employment in the Medical Council of India stand terminated with immediate effect:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such officer or employee of the Medical Council of India shall be entitled to such`
  line `compensation for the premature termination of his employment, which shall not be less than three months'`
  line `pay and allowances, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding the repeal of the aforesaid enactment, any order made, any licence to practice`
  line `issued, any registration made, any permission to start new medical college or to start higher course of`
  line `studies or for increase in the admission capacity granted, any recognition of medical qualifications`
  line `granted, under the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956), which are in force as on the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, shall continue to be in force till the date of their expiry for all purposes, as if`
  line `they had been issued or granted under the provisions of this Act or the rules or regulations made`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (49585)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Transitory provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879&sectionId=49585&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00022_201930_1568010505879
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall be the successor in interest to the Medical`
  line `Council of India including its subsidiaries or owned trusts and all the assets and liabilities of the Medical`
  line `Council of India shall be deemed to have been transferred to the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956), the`
  line `educational standards, requirements and other provisions of the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 and the`
  line `rules and regulations made thereunder shall continue to be in force and operate till new standards or`
  line `requirements are specified under this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that anything done or any action taken as regards the educational standards and`
  line `requirements under the enactment under repeal and the rules and regulations made thereunder shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act and shall continue in`
  line `force accordingly unless and until superseded by anything done or by any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
